Brazilian Stock Movers: Embraer, Gol Linhas Aereas, Itau, Tim

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-05-03T14:38:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/brazilian-stock-movers-embraer-gol-linhas-aereas-itau-tim.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:51 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index lost 0.7 percent to 64,991.74.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) gained 5.4 percent to 13.12 reais.
The world’s fourth-largest aircraft maker said first-quarter
profit rose almost fourfold to 174.3 million reais ($109.6
million) from a year earlier.  Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA (GOLL4)  (GOLL4 BS) declined 1.8
percent to 21.40 reais.  Brazil ’s biggest airline by market value
predicts its first-quarter earnings will be cut by a one-time,
120 million-real charge related to the implementation of a new
system of revenue accounting, according to a regulatory filing.  Itau Unibanco Holding SA (ITUB4)  (ITUB4 BS) fell 1.5 percent to
36.02 reais.  Latin America ’s biggest bank by market value said
adjusted net income, which excludes one-time charges, rose 15
percent to 3.64 billion reais from a year earlier. That’s in
line with the mean estimate for an adjusted profit of 3.58
billion reais in a Bloomberg survey of eight analysts.  Tim Participacoes SA (TCSL4)  (TCSL4 BS) slid 0.7 percent to 7.09
reais. The Brazilian unit of  Italy ’s largest phone company
reported first-quarter net income of 213 million reais,
according to a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
